<promed@promedmail.org>
[Wyoming is a relatively large state and sparsely populated. An increase in
rabies recognizable to county officials is an indication of an increase in
this viral disease. The county must be applauded for its proactive steps to
safeguard pets an human lives and control the disease. However, farm
animals, horses and cattle, are equally susceptible to the disease. Since
these animals have interactions with humans, it is would be prudent to
vaccinate these animals. It is cheap insurance compared to a human life. -
Mod.TG]
